2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for collision checking, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper extensively uses machine learning techniques for collision checking and classifier building. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper presents a real application of motion planning in plant phenotyping, which involves computer vision techniques. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with motion planning in a multi-robot system, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
